/target
**/*.rs.bk
Cargo.lock
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo

# ix-voicings: raw GA CLI JSONL dumps can get huge at full corpus;
# keep a small sample corpus + features checked in, ignore the raw stream
# and any voicings artifacts over the checked-in sample size.
/state/voicings/raw/*.jsonl
!/state/voicings/raw/.gitkeep
state/voicings/*-corpus.json
state/voicings/*-features.json
# Exceptions: guitar-corpus.json is a deliberate ~80KB tracked fixture
# consumed by the adversarial QA workflow (.github/workflows/adversarial-qa.yml)
# for Layer 1 grounding. If a corpus rebuild bombs it past 1MB, untrack
# the bombed copy and restore the canonical via `git checkout HEAD --`.
!state/voicings/guitar-corpus.json

# Adversarial QA: regenerable from CI
state/adversarial/findings.jsonl
state/adversarial/summary.json

# TARS knowledge graph logs — rebuilt from claims ingest
state/graph/

# ix-autoresearch: per-run logs are noisy (one JSONL per overnight session);
# only milestones/ is tracked, populated via `ix-autoresearch promote`.
state/autoresearch/runs/*
!state/autoresearch/runs/.gitkeep

# ix-voicings viz: t-SNE / cluster / neighbor JSON outputs are regenerable
# from the OPTIC-K corpus (cargo run -p ix-voicings --example tsne_export).
# Layouts can be 100MB+, so keep them out of the tree.
state/viz/
